Date: 19 Sep 2000 12:04:54 GMT
From: M. Cosgriff <mcosgriff@hotmail.com>
Source: Khaleej Times 19 Sep 2000 [edited

UAE declared free from Rift Valley Fever
---------------------------------------
The General Secretariat of Municipalities (GSM) yesterday held a meeting of
senior officials from the ministries of Health and Agriculture and Fisheries
and municipalities to discuss preventive measures against Rift Valley
fever, caused by a mosquito-borne virus, which claimed 16 lives in Jazan
[Jizan city in southern Saudi Arabia last week.
Dr Mahmoud Fikri, Assistant Under-Secretary for Preventive Medicine at the
Ministry of Health, who attended the Dubai meeting, issued a statement
saying that the UAE is completely free from Rift Valley fever.
Dr Fekri said that there were continuous contacts with Saudi health
authorities to follow up the situation there.
The virus is transmitted from livestock to humans through mosquitoes and
causes diarrhoea, nausea, and internal bleeding that can result in the
patient's death. The meeting was attended by, among others, Under-Secretary
of the Ministry of Agriculture and Fisheries Rashid Mohammed Khalfan Al
Sharqi, General Secretary of GSM Jassim Mohammed bin Darwish and Assistant
General Secretary of GSM Obied bin Essa.
The participants discussed the various [routes of transmission of Rift
Valley fever and other diseases from animals to human beings. They also
discussed
the quarantine regulations and inspection measures with regard to the
import of livestock. They underscored the need for effective coordination
and cooperation among government organisations for taking preventive
measures. The meeting decided to direct the Ministry of Health to issue a
statement on Rift Valley Fever and the preventive measures being taken
against its spread in the UAE.
The Ministry of Agriculture and Fisheries will issue a decision on
preventing the entry of imported animals with suspected diseases.
The municipalities will also take strict measures to check the meat
imported from various countries.
