Date: Wed. 20 Sep 2000 14:54 EST
From: ProMED-mail
Source: The Gulf Times 20 Sep 2000 [edited

Ministry rules out Saudi meat ban
---------------------------------
The Ministry of Public Health has said it would not ban imports of meat and
livestock from Saudi Arabia following the outbreak of the Rift Valley fever
which reportedly claimed some 30 people in Jizan region, south of the kingdom.
A ministry official said following contacts with Saudi health authorities
for further information about the viral disease, specialists from the
ministry examined the data and found out it was not possible for the fever
to spread in Qatar as the country lacked 2 key factors: mosquitoes and
round-the-year rain, essentially needed for the virus to grow.
Based on that, official concluded, there was no reason for precautionary
measures.
Meanwhile, reports from Dubai quoted UAE health officials as saying on
Monday precautionary measures would be taken to prevent the fever from
reaching the country.
